`config.bst` at the project root controls build settings. It is one self-contained compile-time source file with no source imports.

### A minimal config

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    project #= |
        name = "my_project",
        entry_root = "src",
    |

    html #= |
        dev_output = "dev",
        release_output = "release",
    |
]

### Structure

- One required `project` record provides project identity and settings.
- `project.name` is required for stable identity.
- Builder sections like `html` hold builder-specific settings.
- The command selects the builder before config validation. `config.bst` does not select the builder.
- Only active sections are schema-validated.

### Remember

- Only `config.bst` has config semantics.
- Values must be compile-time constants.
- Output settings are builder-owned, not global project fields.